-- DRB Shareholders Approve Purchase of 42.7% of Proton
-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 2012-03-14T07:57:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/drb-shareholders-approve-purchase-of-42-7-of-proton-correct-.html
(Corrects stake of extra purchase in second paragraph.)  DRB-Hicom Bhd. (DRB) ’s shareholders
approved the company’s plan to buy a controlling 42.7 percent
stake in  Proton Holdings Bhd. (PROH)  for 1.29 billion ringgit ($425
million) from Khazanah Nasional Bhd.  DRB will complete the purchase of the state-owned carmaker
in seven days, according to a company statement. Proton will
become a 50-percent owned subsidiary, it said. DRB bought an
additional 7.3 percent stake in Proton from the open market in
January.  To contact the reporter on this story:
